# Front-End Component Structure (Web)

Applies to [`apps/web`](apps/web) only — Vite, React, TypeScript, Tailwind v4, shadcn/ui, React Query, Vitest.

Keep [`App.tsx`](apps/web/src/App.tsx) thin: gate views (e.g. onboarding vs dashboard) and compose feature components — no business logic or fetch code in the app shell.

## Directory layout

```
apps/web/src/
├── App.tsx                 # View switching / route shell
├── main.tsx                # Providers (QueryClient, UserProvider)
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                 # shadcn primitives only (Button, Card, Table, …)
│   ├── Dashboard.tsx       # Feature / page-level components
│   └── OnboardingView.tsx
├── contexts/               # React context providers (e.g. UserProvider)
├── lib/
│   ├── api.ts              # fetch wrappers → /api (via Vite proxy)
│   ├── format-money.ts     # Display helpers
│   ├── user-storage.ts     # Client persistence (localStorage)
│   └── utils.ts            # cn() and shared utilities
├── pages/                  # Optional page wrappers (wire from App when added)
└── test/
    ├── setup.ts
    └── test-utils.tsx      # renderWithProviders
```

| Location | Use for |
|----------|---------|
| `components/` | Feature and page-level UI (`Dashboard`, `OnboardingView`) |
| `components/ui/` | Shared shadcn primitives — never feature-specific logic |
| `contexts/` | Cross-cutting client state (`useUser`, providers) |
| `lib/` | API clients, formatters, storage — no JSX |
| `packages/shared` | Domain types (`User`, `Statement`, …) via `@financial-healthcheck/shared` |

Import shared domain types from `@financial-healthcheck/shared`. Do not duplicate API shapes in component-local types unless they are view-only props.

## Component files

Co-locate tests next to the component: `Dashboard.tsx` + `Dashboard.test.tsx`.

For small features, a single file per component is fine. When a component grows (multiple sub-views, hooks, schemas), promote to a folder:

```
components/
  Dashboard/
    Dashboard.tsx
    Dashboard.test.tsx
    components/
      StatementTable/
        StatementTable.tsx
        StatementTable.test.tsx
```

- **Nest** sub-components under the parent's `components/` when only that parent uses them.
- **Promote** to `components/<Name>/` at the top level when a second parent imports them.
- Do not put feature components inside `components/ui/`.

## Server state (React Query)

Use TanStack React Query for all API data. Do not use `useEffect` + `useState` for fetching.

| Layer | Location | Responsibility |
|-------|----------|----------------|
| API client | `lib/api.ts` | `fetch` calls; use `STATEMENT_API_ROUTES` / types from shared |
| Components | `components/*.tsx` | `useQuery` / `useMutation`; render loading, error, empty, data |
| App root | `main.tsx` | `QueryClientProvider` |

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — fetch in useEffect
useEffect(() => {
  fetchStatements(userId).then(setStatements);
}, [userId]);

// ✅ GOOD — React Query in the component
const { data, isLoading, isError, refetch } = useQuery({
  queryKey: ["statements", user.id],
  queryFn: () => fetchStatements(user.id),
  enabled: !!user,
});
```

- Invalidate or refetch via query keys after mutations — do not manually sync duplicate state.
- Handle all four UI states: loading, error (with retry), empty, and success.

## Client state

- **User session** — `contexts/UserProvider` + `lib/user-storage.ts` (localStorage, includes `user.id` for API calls).
- **Server data** — React Query only; never store API responses in context.

## Forms

- Simple single-field flows (e.g. onboarding name) may use controlled `useState`.
- Multi-field forms: prefer **react-hook-form** + **Zod** with a colocated `*.schema.ts` when added to the project.
- Validate API request bodies on the server; mirror rules in client schemas when using forms.

## Styling

- Use Tailwind utility classes and shadcn components from `components/ui/`.
- Use theme tokens from [`index.css`](apps/web/src/index.css) (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-primary`, …) — warm palette is already configured.
- Use `cn()` from `lib/utils.ts` for conditional class names.

## Shared UI

Compose from `components/ui/` (Button, Card, Table, Input, Badge). Add new primitives via the shadcn CLI into `components/ui/` — do not copy primitive markup into feature components.

Use TanStack Table for tabular data (see `Dashboard` statements table).

## Testing

| Type | Location | Approach |
|------|----------|----------|
| Unit | `components/*.test.tsx` | Vitest + React Testing Library |
| E2E | `tests/e2e/` | Playwright |

- Use `renderWithProviders` from [`test/test-utils.tsx`](apps/web/src/test/test-utils.tsx) — wraps `QueryClientProvider` and `UserProvider`.
- Mock `globalThis.fetch` for API-dependent component tests.
- Seed `localStorage` via `USER_STORAGE_KEY` when tests need a logged-in user.
- Re-export RTL helpers from `test-utils` (`screen`, `waitFor`, `userEvent`).

```bash
pnpm --filter @financial-healthcheck/web test:unit
pnpm test:e2e
```

## When to split

Extract a sub-component when:

- JSX is reused or the parent exceeds ~100 lines
- A section has a clear responsibility (table, form, empty state, error card)
- Logic can be tested via a pure helper in `lib/` (e.g. `format-money.ts`)

Keep fetch hooks and query keys in the feature component until a dedicated `api/hooks/` layer is introduced.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — monolithic App with fetch, table, and form
export function App() {
  const [statements, setStatements] = useState([]);
  useEffect(() => { /* fetch */ }, []);
  return (/* 150 lines */);
}

// ✅ GOOD — thin App, composed features
export function App() {
  const { user } = useUser();
  return user ? <Dashboard /> : <OnboardingView />;
}
```
